article_title: Covered California adds 425,000 new enrollees, sees increase in younger residents
article_text:
More 18- to 34-year-olds sign up for Obamacare health coverage

Breakdowns by ethnicity, type of plan and geographic areas not yet available

Overall, California’s 1.6 million are among 12.7 million Obamacare enrollees nationwide

article_metadata.news-keywords: Covered California, open enrollment, health care insurance, peter lee, obamacare, affordable care act
article_metadata.description: More than 425,000 Californians – including a bigger percentage of younger residents – signed up for new health insurance policies by last week’s Obamacare enrollment deadline, Covered California officials announced Thursday.
